<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Skyway Ground Crew · Profile</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="challenge-page">
    <a href="/challenge/8" class="back-link">← Back to Day 8</a>
    <div class="brand brand-sm">
      <span class="brand-mark">⛨</span>
      <span>CySER Workshop · Skyway engagement</span>
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-header">
      <h1>Profile</h1>
      <p class="desc">Server-decoded view of your JWT.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-content">
      <h2>Decoded payload</h2>
      <pre class="code-block"><%= JSON.stringify(payload, null, 2) %></pre>

      <h2>Your raw token</h2>
      <pre class="code-block" style="word-break:break-all; white-space:pre-wrap;"><%= rawToken %></pre>

      <% if (denied) { %>
        <div class="result-msg error" style="display:block; margin: 18px 0;">
          Access to <code>/challenge/8/admin</code> denied: your role is "<%= payload.role %>", admin required.
        </div>
      <% } %>

      <div class="tools-section">
        <h3>Next step</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>You can't re-sign HS256 without the server's secret. Don't bother trying</li>
          <li>But you <em>can</em> hand-craft an <code>alg: "none"</code> token. Skyway's verifier accepts it</li>
          <li>See the Console one-liner on <a href="/challenge/8">Day 8</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div style="display:flex; gap:14px; margin-top: 22px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/challenge/8/admin" class="play-btn">Try /admin →</a>
        <form method="POST" action="/challenge/8/logout" style="margin:0;">
          <button type="submit" class="play-btn" style="background:#888;">Log out</button>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
